      "content": "it just feels like toxic positivity tbh. like, \"resilience\" doesn't stop the ice caps from melting or the ecosystems from collapsing. it feels like we're just being told to stay in a burning building because the view is nice. if the end is inevitable, isn't it just more logical to just... opt out now instead of suffering through the decay?",
